body:
### Description

I'm using Skiasharp for annotating an image. Currently i'm facing a issue on saving the image from the canvas. 
I will load the image as per its size. But i'm keeping the canvas to full screen size. While saving any small image my code is saving the image and the canvas which is set to full screen. As a result i'm getting Extra spaces from either side of the image (given that image is loaded center in my UI).
Please could you suggest some idea on how to save only the annotated image irrespective of the Canvas size?

### Code
private void OnCanvasViewPaintSurface(object sender, SKPaintSurfaceEventArgs args)
{
surface = args.Surface;
canvas = args.Surface.Canvas;

//Load the image to the canvas
SKSize imgSize = new SKSize(m_bitmap.bitmap.Width, m_bitmap.bitmap.Height);
SKRect aspectRect = SKRect.Create(args.Info.Width, args.Info.Height).AspectFit(imgSize);
canvas.DrawBitmap(m_bitmap.bitmap, aspectRect, null);

//Saving image from the canvas
m_skImage = surface.Snapshot();
data = m_skImage.Encode(SKEncodedImageFormat.Png, 80);
ResultImageStream = data.AsStream();
imageStream = new MemoryStream();
ResultImageStream.CopyTo(imageStream);
ResultData = imageStream.ToArray();
}

### Expected Behavior

Save only the image with the annotation.

### Actual Behavior

Save the image with annotation and also with the Blank spaces

### Basic Information

- Version :  1.57.0
- IDE:  Visual Studio
- Platform Target Frameworks: <!-- all that apply, remove the platforms that aren't broken or haven't had any testing -->
  - Android:  4.4 and above
  - iOS:  10.4 and above
  - UWP:  16299
